column1: A cool air wedge remains entrenched over central NC today bringing drizzle and
moderate NE winds.  The wedge should begin to break down overnight as warmer
southwest winds signal the approach of the next storm system on Thursday.  Sig
nificant rain totals are possible by Friday afternoon in the Triad although th
e heaviest precipitation field may remain to the northwest.  The weekend shoul
d be dry before another storm system swings through on Monday.  Air quality re
adings should remain clean during this active weather pattern with all polluta
nts remaining in the Code Green (WEINSTOCK).
Air quality levels have increased a little today despite the continuous shower
s throughout the region.  Levels do, however, remain in the GREEN range.  Sout
hwest winds are causing this slight increase but as an approaching low moves c
loser to the Triad winds will become fairly strong and cause numbers to drop o
nce again.  Winds should slowly shift to the northwest which will decrease val
ues further.  Levels should remain in the GREEN range throughout the period.
